Implemented Vercel Web Analytics for the project

## Changes Made

### Installed Package
- Added `@vercel/analytics@2.0.1` to project dependencies using yarn

### Modified Files

1. **frontend/package.json**
   - Added `@vercel/analytics` as a direct dependency

2. **frontend/src/App.js**
   - Imported `Analytics` component from `@vercel/analytics/react`
   - Added `<Analytics />` component to the App component JSX (placed after the Toaster component)

3. **frontend/yarn.lock**
   - Updated with new dependency information for `@vercel/analytics`

## Implementation Details

Following the official Vercel Analytics quickstart documentation (https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart), I:
1. Fetched the latest installation instructions from Vercel's documentation
2. Identified this as a Create React App project
3. Used the React-specific integration: imported from `@vercel/analytics/react`
4. Added the Analytics component to the main App component where it will be rendered on all pages

The Analytics component has been placed at the root level of the application, ensuring that page views and analytics events are tracked across all routes (Home, History, and Room pages).

## Verification

- Build completed successfully with `yarn build`
- No errors or warnings introduced
- The Analytics component is now integrated and will track page views when deployed to Vercel

## Next Steps

After deployment to Vercel:
1. Enable Web Analytics in the Vercel dashboard (Analytics section)
2. Verify analytics tracking by checking the Network tab for requests to `/_vercel/insights/*`
3. View analytics data in the Vercel dashboard
